lead_paragraph: As Southern California endured another drenching today, two tourists were killed when they were buried when a rain-soaked cliff collapsed, and a surfer may have been swept away by storm-tossed seas. Periods of heavy rain through Tuesday were expected to leave 2 inches along the coast and up to 8 inches at lower elevations in the mountains.

headline.main: Heavy Rain Hits Southern California Again
